==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} diminutive of ''scrofa'': a breeding sow, because swine were supposed to be subject to the complaint; or by [[fanciful]] comparison of the glandular swellings to little pigs.
===Noun===
'''scrofulide'''
#(Rare): Any [[affliction]] of the skin dependent on [[scrofula]].
#* '''1870''': Title ''American Journal of Syphilography and Dermatology'': Publisher F.W. Christern: "After recovery from [[tinea tonsurans]]...crusts and [[epidermic]] [[exfoliation]]s form on the scalp. It is a benign '''scrofulide''' induced by the [[trycophyton]]."